## Step 4: Add environment variables to Railway

In Railway dashboard → Variables:

```bash
# Master switch (set to 'false' to disable ALL AI features)
AI_ENABLED=true

# Individual feature flags
AI_EXTRACTION_ENABLED=true
AI_QUERY_UNDERSTANDING_ENABLED=false
AI_CONTRADICTION_DETECTION=false
AI_KNOWLEDGE_CONSOLIDATION_ENABLED=false
AI_RETRIEVAL_RERANKING_ENABLED=false
AI_SESSION_MEMORY_ENABLED=false
AI_ONTOLOGY_REFLECTION_ENABLED=false
AI_CHARACTER_RESPONSE_ENABLED=false
AI_DOCUMENT_SUMMARIZATION_ENABLED=false

# FreeLLM configuration (FREE!)
FREELLM_API_KEY=your-key-here
FREELLM_BASE_URL=https://freellm.com/api/v1
FREELLM_MODEL=gpt-4o

# Optional: Gradual rollout (0-100%)
AI_GRADUAL_ROLLOUT_PERCENT=100

# Optional: Logging
AI_LOG_ALL=false
AI_LOG_EXTRACTION=true
```

